    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nMany LSP-related features require snippet expansion.\n\nI think neovim defines `vim.ui.*` as extension points in the ecosystem.\n\n`vim.snippet.expand` is the built-in implementation of snippet functionality, is it appropriate for the community to override it?\n\nSo how about defining `vim.ui.snippet.expand` or `vim.ui.expand_snippet` as extension points for snippet extensions, and using `vim.ui.snippet.expand` when snippet expansion is required in neovim core?\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nneovim has extension point that expanding snippet and the user can choose they favorite snippet plugin.",
